{
  "texts": [
    "Mobile applications development in local language for facilitating access to local and cross-border buyers could also be a possible solution.",
    "Furthermore, developing policy support by regulatory bodies could enhance trust, security, and access for buyers and sellers alike.",
    "Additionally, microlearning or small training sessions with practical examples could elevate the literacy rate and market negotiation skills among small-scale farmers.",
    "• Lastly, lack of interdisciplinary collaboration could be another significant challenge in AI adoption for agriculture.",
    "Generally, AI implementation for agriculture requires cooperation among experts in data science, economics, agronomy, engineering, policy making, social science, and AI, which often lacks in developing countries."
  ]
}